Method Detail

cancelCurrentTask

public boolean cancelCurrentTask(int msToWait)
                          throws java.lang.InterruptedException
Requests the currently running task to stop and waits until it is finished.

Parameters:
msToWait - Time to wait for the current task to finish.
Returns:
True if current task is no longer running, false if it is non-interruptible or the timeout period elapsed.
Throws:
java.lang.InterruptedException - If waiting for the current task to finish/cancel is interrupted.

setIdleTask

public void setIdleTask(AntChannelTask task)
Sets the task to be run whenever there is no active task. If the executor is started and there is no active task it is started immediately. This task will be interrupted whenever another task is requested to be run, so it must implement AntChannelTask.handleInterruptRequest(int)!!! Pass null as the argument to cancel the current idle task.

Parameters:
task - The task to run when the executor is not processing other tasks, must implement AntChannelTask.handleInterruptRequest(int)!!! Can set to null to clear idle task.

shutdown

public com.dsi.ant.channel.AntChannel shutdown(boolean releaseChannel)
Attempts to interrupt any current task, stop the worker thread, and optionally return or release the underlying ANT channel. Current tasks are requested to interrupt and given up to 3s to finish before the channel is released anyway.

Note: If this is called from within the task doWork thread, it does attempt to interrupt the current task. In this case you should clear any chained tasks attached to the current task or they will attempt to run.

Parameters:
releaseChannel - false to attempt to get the active channel returned, true to release the channel and return null
Returns:
The underlying ANT channel. Will be null if the shutdown was not clean, the executor is already shutdown or releaseChannel was set to true.

startTask

public boolean startTask(AntChannelTask task,
                         int msToWaitOnCurrentTask)
                  throws java.lang.InterruptedException
Attempts to start the provided task on this executor.

Parameters:
task - The task to execute.
msToWaitOnCurrentTask - Time to wait for the current task to finish if there is one.
Returns:
True if the task was started. False if another task is still running.
Throws:
java.lang.InterruptedException - If waiting for the current task to finish/cancel is interrupted.
